{"source_slug":"ethan-glover","target_slug":"aerys-ii-targaryen","target_type":"character.human","evidence_paragraph":"When «Brandon Stark» learned of his sister «Lyanna's» abduction at the hands of «Rhaegar Targaryen», «Prince of Dragonstone», he took off for «King's Landing» with «Jeffory Mallister», «Kyle Royce», «Elbert Arryn», and his squire, Ethan. When Brandon entered the «Red Keep» and demanded that Rhaegar come out and die, King «Aerys II Targaryen» had Brandon's party arrested for threatening the life of the crown prince. The fathers of Brandon and his companions were called to King's Landing to answer for the crimes of their sons. The king had the fathers and sons all executed, with only Ethan spared. Aerys then demanded that «Jon Arryn», «Lord of the Eyrie», execute his «wards», «Robert Baratheon», «Lord of Storm's End», and Brandon's younger brother «Eddard Stark», now «Lord of Winterfell». However, Jon refused the king's command, and «Robert's Rebellion» started shortly thereafter.","source_section":"## Narrative Arc / ### A Clash of Kings"}
